2026-05-22T03:32:00Z gmm-independent-evaluation
- Workflow skill: kernel-eval-workflow, continued from high-priority TODO "GroupedMatmul routing data missing".
- Design: treat GroupedMatmul as an independent kernel family. Keep the theoretical ordinary MatMul lower bound only as a compatibility/reference field, and add two explicit routing scenarios because kernel_details.csv does not expose group_list.
- Model: balanced scenario spreads tokens across min(expert_count, M) active experts; extreme_imbalance routes all tokens to one expert. Both scenarios charge active expert weight traffic, activation/output traffic, quant auxiliary bytes, Cube core work-tile occupancy, and dtype/quant compute peak where available.
